            <config><repeats><repeat count="8" name="rqm_sam_region_regfile"/></repeats><busdomains><busdomain name="default_map" bus="CUSTOM" addressUnit="8" offset="0" address="0x014" endaddress="0x93" size="16" address2="0x024"/></busdomains></config><doc>The RQM SAM region configuration.
For the RQM to be functional, the SAM must be configured.
The SAM can be configured even during ACTIVE state, after config_done has been asserted.
To configure the SAM after config_done has been asserted, SW needs to:
1.Ensure there are no more transactions to this region.
2.Disable the region.
3.Config the region
4.Enable the region</doc><reg name="cfg_rqm_region_start" refNameID="cfg_rqm_region_start" uid="2026-05-1511:36:28T0f75acce-d1bc-47af-a363-798b2d5cad09" keypath="slc_output_stage_regfile.csr_slc_rqm.rqm_sam_region_regfile.cfg_rqm_region_start,csr_slc_rqm.rqm_sam_region_regfile.cfg_rqm_region_start,rqm_sam_region_regfile.cfg_rqm_region_start,cfg_rqm_region_start" hwmapaddr="9" csize="4" offset="0" caddress="0" address="0x014" endaddress="0x17" size="4" address_dec="20" heading="1.6.1.1" child_no="1" default="0x00000000" sw="rw" hw="ro">
