        <section name="cfg_rate_limiter_regfile" refNameID="cfg_rate_limiter_regfile" uid="2026-05-1511:36:28T87e736ba-f38f-4c49-885e-86ddf499e037" keypath="slc_output_stage_regfile.csr_slc_rqm.cfg_rate_limiter_regfile,csr_slc_rqm.cfg_rate_limiter_regfile,cfg_rate_limiter_regfile" keypathdown="cfg_rate_limiter_regfile.cfg_rqm_rate_limiter,cfg_rqm_rate_limiter" count="2" hwmapaddr="35" max_reg_size="32" csize="32" offset="896" caddress="896" address="0x394" endaddress="0x3B3" size="16" address_dec="916" address2="0x3A4" heading="1.6.14" child_no="17">
            <config><repeats><repeat count="2" name="cfg_rate_limiter_regfile"/></repeats><busdomains><busdomain name="default_map" bus="CUSTOM" addressUnit="8" offset="896" address="0x394" endaddress="0x3B3" size="16" address2="0x3A4"/></busdomains></config><doc>For SLC :
We have 2 vectors, cfg_rate_limiter_regfile[0] is used when throttling_bit = 0,
cfg_rate_limiter_regfile[1] is used when throttling_bit = 1.
For Non SLC :
We have 12 vectors, and the vector we use is based on the CBusy and the req color.
Vectors mapping :
4'd0 - CBusy 00, Green Rate limiter vector.
4'd1 - CBusy 00, Yellow Rate limiter vector.
4'd2 - CBusy 00, Red Rate limiter vector.
4'd3 - CBusy 01, Green Rate limiter vector.
4'd4 - CBusy 01, Yellow Rate limiter vector.
4'd5 - CBusy 01, Red Rate limiter vector.
4'd6 - CBusy 10, Green Rate limiter vector.
4'd7 - CBusy 10, Yellow Rate limiter vector.
4'd8 - CBusy 10, Red Rate limiter vector.
4'd9 - CBusy 11, Green Rate limiter vector.
4'd10 - CBusy 11, Yellow Rate limiter vector.
4'd11 - CBusy 11, Red Rate limiter vector.</doc><reg name="cfg_rqm_rate_limiter" refNameID="cfg_rqm_rate_limiter" uid="2026-05-1511:36:28T9ec6de6d-5544-486a-a361-a04d4600e1aa" keypath="slc_output_stage_regfile.csr_slc_rqm.cfg_rate_limiter_regfile.cfg_rqm_rate_limiter,csr_slc_rqm.cfg_rate_limiter_regfile.cfg_rqm_rate_limiter,cfg_rate_limiter_regfile.cfg_rqm_rate_limiter,cfg_rqm_rate_limiter" count="4" hwmapaddr="36" csize="16" offset="0" caddress="0" address="0x394" endaddress="0x3A3" size="4" address_dec="916" address2="0x398" heading="1.6.14.1" child_no="1" default="0xFFFFFFFF" sw="rw" hw="ro">
                <config><repeats><repeat count="4" name="cfg_rqm_rate_limiter"/></repeats><busdomains><busdomain name="default_map" bus="CUSTOM" addressUnit="8" offset="0" address="0x394" endaddress="0x3A3" size="4" address2="0x398"/></busdomains><regwidth>32</regwidth></config><field name="vector" offset="31:0" uid="2026-05-1511:36:28T70e6e497-08df-40c0-9e28-90b8921b31b7" keypath="slc_output_stage_regfile.csr_slc_rqm.cfg_rate_limiter_regfile.cfg_rqm_rate_limiter.vector,csr_slc_rqm.cfg_rate_limiter_regfile.cfg_rqm_rate_limiter.vector,cfg_rate_limiter_regfile.cfg_rqm_rate_limiter.vector,cfg_rqm_rate_limiter.vector,vector">
                    <doc>Rate limiter bit map.
the limiter runs over these bits in a cycle,
enabling a request only when a bit is set (e.g. if we want a 50% rate limiter,
we will set only the even bits).
The bitmap[reg_index][bitmap_j] corresponds to 32 * reg_index + bitmap_j</doc>
                    <sw>rw</sw>
                    <hw>ro</hw>
                    <default unresolvedDef="4294967295">11111111111111111111111111111111</default>
                </field>
            </reg>
            
        </section>
        
        
        <emptyspace address="0x3B4" endaddress="0x3D3" heading="1.6.18" child_no="18"><config><busdomains><busdomain name="default_map" bus="CUSTOM" addressUnit="8" address="0x3B4" endaddress="0x3D3" address2="0x3D8"/></busdomains></config></emptyspace><reg name="cfg_rqm_miphb_read_opcodes" refNameID="cfg_rqm_miphb_read_opcodes" uid="2026-05-1511:36:28T1d5143e8-fd5f-4b5c-a482-c6e9620b5c6d" keypath="slc_output_stage_regfile.csr_slc_rqm.cfg_rqm_miphb_read_opcodes,csr_slc_rqm.cfg_rqm_miphb_read_opcodes,cfg_rqm_miphb_read_opcodes" count="4" hwmapaddr="39" csize="16" offset="960" caddress="960" address="0x3D4" endaddress="0x3E3" size="4" address_dec="980" address2="0x3D8" heading="1.6.15" child_no="19" default="0x00000000" sw="rw" hw="ro">
